(2404, 517, 1473, 'Oh yes. In fact, the older I get the more I understand the many proverbs I heard my father say.<br />\nSince there were no writing systems and book publishing, I can say that the tribal wisdom was encoded in thousands of proverbs, songs and mythological stories. Then passed down from generation to generation. <br />\n<br />\nFor instance, after watching the movie Black Panther, I began to reflect deeply on the words of a song I sang many times as a child: \"Do not touch the tail of a leopard, whether the leopard is alive or dead\"', NULL, 0, '', 1, '2018-03-19 05:49:26'),
