(653, 1566, 'The Term EDUCATION needs to be defined, to be useful. I REJECT the white or european  idea of  earning a college or university degree as being EDUCATED.<br />\nI learned that for Black people it is more useful to embrace one of the African definitions  of education. For example I utilize the East African definition of Education found in Jomo Kenyatta\'s book: Facing Mt Kenya. Definition is \"You Start Learning when you are born and you Stop learning when you DieI\"  As a former Business Instructor  part of my research revealed that to be successful in business you don\'t need a college or university degree!<br />\nI will provide proof and examples in other Posts.', NULL, 0, '', 0, '2018-06-07 05:25:49', 0),
(654, 1566, 'We need to start and operate African cafes in the USA and other countries. <br />\nWe need to start lobbying our Black African coffee farmers  and work-out special relationships for the African coffee bean resource. Starbucks is opening a New coffee location in China every 16-hours.  How many Black people are opening Coffee/Bakeries Cafes in China? Africa? USA? You don\'t<br />\nneed a white university degree to start and manage a successful coffee cafe business. Courses on Sanitation is a must for this type of enterprise.<br />\nWork at Starbucks and learn what you need to know to start your own coffee business               Let me know what you think?<br />\nOne Love!', NULL, 0, '', 0, '2018-06-07 05:37:38', 0),
